metadata.author: Opentrons QA
metadata.description:
This is a FLEX protocol for Illumina DNA Prep for up to 48 samples. This protocol's workflow starts with the Tagmentation of input DNA and proceeds to Bead Cleanup of the final libraries. A higher throughput version, that still uses Multichannels, can be found here: Illumina DNA Prep 96x

A lower throughput 24x version of this protocol for the OT2 can be found here. Illumina DNA Prep 24x for OT2

Depending on the number of samples selected the protocol can be either walkaway or require user intervention to reset tipracks.
Illumina DNA Prep Reference Guide
